net.jhoogland.jautomata

Class Automata

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.jhoogland.jautomata.Automata

  • public class Automata
extends Object
    This class contains static methods for computing properties of automata, creating various types of automata, and performing weight computations on automata.
    Author:
    Jasper Hoogland

        public static <L,K> Map<Object,K> shortestDistancesFromInitialStates(Automaton<L,K> automaton,
                                                     SingleSourceShortestDistancesInterface<K> sssd)

      • shortestDistancesToFinalStates

        public static <L,K> Map<Object,K> shortestDistancesToFinalStates(ReverselyAccessibleAutomaton<L,K> automaton,
                                                 SingleSourceShortestDistancesInterface<K> sssd)
        Computes for each state s the shortest distance from s to the final states. The automaton is required to be reversely accessible.
        Parameters:
        automaton - the automaton to perform the operation on
        sssd - the shortest distance algorithm to use
        Returns:
        a map that assigns to each state the shortest distance from that state to the final states
